SimpleFieldSet

public SimpleFieldSet(boolean shortLived)
Create a SimpleFieldSet.

Parameters:
shortLived - If false, strings will be interned to ensure that they use as little memory as possible. Only set to true if the SFS will be short-lived or small.

SimpleFieldSet

public SimpleFieldSet(BufferedReader br,
                      boolean allowMultiple,
                      boolean shortLived)
               throws IOException
Construct a SimpleFieldSet from reading a BufferedReader.

Parameters:
br -
allowMultiple - If true, multiple lines with the same field name will be combined; if false, the constructor will throw.
shortLived - If false, strings will be interned to ensure that they use as little memory as possible. Only set to true if the SFS will be short-lived or small.
Throws:
IOException - If the buffer could not be read, or if there was a formatting problem.

putAppend

public void putAppend(String key,
                      String value)
Aggregating put. Set a key to a value, if the value already exists, append to it. If you do not need this functionality please use putOverwrite for a minimal performance gain.

Parameters:
key - The key.
value - The value.

putOverwrite

public void putOverwrite(String key,
                         String value)
Set a key to a value, overwriting any existing value if present. This function is a little bit faster than putAppend() because it does not check whether the key already exists.

Parameters:
key - The key.
value - The value.

removeSubset

public void removeSubset(String key)
It removes the specified subset. For example, in a SimpleFieldSet like this: foo=bar foo.bar=foobar foo.bar.boo=foobarboo calling it with the parameter "foo" means to drop the second and the third line.

Parameters:
is - the subset to remove
